name: integrated battery interface system production, for Li-ion battery | integrated battery interface system, for Li-ion battery | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/24699/documentation

This dataset represents the production of 1 kg integrated battery interface system (IBIS), which is part of the Battery Management System (BMS) of a Li-ion battery. The IBIS is modelled according to the publication of Ellingsen et al. (2014). The IBIS functions include overseeing the battery charge and discharge strategies, providing vehicle-level high voltage ;precharge, contactor control, system isolation monitoring and charge/discharge current measurements. Proxies were used to approximate the production processes. It is assumed that the IBIS is manufactured at an electronic component production plant.;Reference:;Ellingsen, L. A. W., Majeau‐Bettez, G., Singh, B., Srivastava, A. K., Valøen, L. O., & Strømman, A. H. (2014). Life cycle assessment of a lithium‐ion battery vehicle pack. Journal of Industrial Ecology, 18(1), 113-124.

The activity starts with the raw material entering the factory.

The activity ends with the production of the integrated battery interface system at the factory gate.
category: C:Manufacturing/27:Manufacture of electrical equipment/272:Manufacture of batteries and accumulators/2720:Manufacture of batteries and accumulators

processDocumentation.timeDescription: The time period is from 2014 (year of the publication of data) and 2020 (year of the dataset)
processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Original data were provided by the battery producer Miljøbil Grenland, located in Norway, for a Li-ion battery for use in electric vehicles. (Ellingsen et al. 2014, Life cycle assessment of a lithium‐ion battery vehicle pack. Journal of Industrial Ecology, 18(1), 113-124). Geography uncertainty has been adjusted accordingly.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: The integrated battery interface system (IBIS) is an electronic component of the battery management system (BMS), containing printed circuit boards and integrated circuits, clamps and connectors, spacers. It has an important role as master controller for the BMS.
